## Description {#details}

This class represents success/failure for parsing-like operations that find it important to chain together failable operations with <code>||</code>.

This is an extended version of <code><a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/logicalresult">LogicalResult</a></code> that allows for explicit conversion to bool.

This class should not be used for general error handling cases - we prefer to keep the logic explicit with the <code>succeeded</code>/<code>failed</code> predicates. However, traditional monadic-style parsing logic can sometimes get swallowed up in boilerplate without this, so we provide this for narrow cases where it is important.
